description.narrative: The preschool education coverage of 3 – 6 year old children increased from 52% in 2014 to 72.6% in 2018/19, as a result of multi-year reform efforts supported by UNICEF. Despite the overall progress, the number of children from the most vulnerable groups enrolled in early childhood education remains at a low level. Targeted actions were therefore taken to ensure quality support to children with disabilities and to enable access to preschool of Roma children. The latter has contributed to an increase of enrolment of Roma children which has almost doubled since 2018. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/12/2019
